  { q: "Is Fulgor Milano a family-owned company like Bertazzoni?", a: "Yes. Fulgor Milano is owned by the Meneghini family in northern Italy, operating across multiple generations. This gives Fulgor Milano similar family-ownership continuity to Bertazzoni (also family-owned northern Italian since 1882) and ILVE (Berto family Bassano del Grappa since 1953). All three are distinct Italian family manufacturers with separate engineering lineages, separate US distribution networks (Fulgor Milano USA Schaumburg IL; Bertazzoni Englewood Cliffs NJ; Eurochef USA Texas for ILVE), and separate parts chains. For LA customers with Italian-heritage kitchens, the three brands offer different aesthetic and pricing positions within the broader Italian-luxury wall oven category." }
